{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Stop Ltd companies offsetting loan interest or other expenses for rental income",
        "additional_details": "We want the Government to tax Ltd company rental income in the same way an individual gets taxed on property rental income.",
        "background": "We believe there\u2019s a total disparity in an individual buying a house to rent and not being able to offset loan interest payments or refurbishments and updates to property that are considered \u2018capital expenditure\u2019 against rental income, whereas as Ltd company has these tax advantages.",
